<TITLE> SC admits appeal to overturn Khaleda Airbus ruling </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 10 (bdnews24.com)The Supreme Court on Sunday admitted the government petition to overturn the High Court verdict cancelling the corruption case against former prime minister Khaleda Zia over purchase of Airbus planes. Besides, the court also excused the government's delay of 1,655 days to file the appeal. The orders were given by the four-judge bench of the Appellate Division headed by chief justice MM Ruhul Amin. The case was cancelled on the basis of Khaleda's appeal on Sept 10, 2003. The leave to appeal was filed on Mar 23, 2008. The Anticorruption Bureau filed the case with Motijheel police on Aug 30, 1998 charging the her with Tk 140 crore corruption in buying two Airbuses. The appeal was not filed against the High Court verdict since the case was cancelled during the reign of BNP-led government, said deputy attorney general ASM Abdul Mubin in the hearing. TH Khan and Moudud Ahmed took argued in the hearing for Khaleda. They said the High Court verdict was right and the government failed to give a proper explanation for the delay. bd
